msItem.title: Hrólfs saga kraka ok kappa hans
msItem.filiation:
Prersumably the saga was transcribed from a parchment manuscript, cf. e.g. Kålund
Katalog I 9 and Finnur Jónsson
Hrólfs saga kraka og Bjarkarímur i , Slay The Manuscripts of Hrólfs saga kraka , however, consider AM 9 fol a transcript of the paper volume AM 12 b fol, even though deviations between AM 9 fol and AM 12 b fol occur.

Finnur Jónsson, Hrólfs saga kraka og Bjarkarímur
Slay, Hrólfs saga kraka Ed. cit., var.app. (“9”)
msItem.note: The saga is divided into unnumbered chapters. It is, however, divided into þættir with Fróða þáttr as the first.

msItem.title: Fróða þáttr
msItem.incipit:
Madur hiet Halfdan. Enn ann ar Frőde
brædur tveir og Konga sner.
msItem.explicit: Enn vppbyriast fra Hroar og Helga Halfdanar sonum

msItem.rubric:
Af Hroar Og Helga Half
danar Sonum.
msItem.incipit: Kőngur hiet Nordre. Hann ried fyrer nockrum hluta Einglands.
msItem.explicit:
Þau Yrsa unnust mked og attu eirn son þann Hrolfur
hiet / er mykill mæta madur vard sdann

msItem.incipit:
Olof drottning spr ad þau Helge konungr og Yrsa vnntuzt
mked og vna vel rade snv.
msItem.explicit: Og lykur hier þætte Helga kőngs.

title.q: Fra Adels konge Og Yrsu drottningu

msItem.incipit:
Adels kőngur hrosade nv Sigre og þottist
miaug hafa framast er han vann kong so agjæt
ann sem Helge var
msItem.explicit: enn honumm þotte raunar ecke mle skypta þott Suipdagur feinge osigur og stynge nidur nøsumm

msItem.incipit:
Nu buazt þeir brædur j burt og stodar ecke ad hamla
þeim.
msItem.explicit:
Og endar hier Søgu Hrolfs
kongs Kraka / Og kappa hanns.

supportDesc.foliation: Foliation 1-48 in red ink by Kristian Kålund.

layoutDesc.layout: Written in one column with 25-26 lines per page. Running titles. Spaces have been left blank for later insertion of initials.

handDesc.handNote: Written by Jón Erlendsson of Villingaholt. The writing is clear.

physDesc.additions: Marginalia at the first few pages.

binding.p: From between 1700-1730. Full-bound: parchment with with laced-in single endband supports. On the spine, below a green slip, the title: Hrolfs Kraka Saga. is seen, possibly in Arne Magnusson's hand. On the recto of the first flyleaf, below an AM-slip, Kålund wrote the date 5/6 - 85. The size of the binding is 307 202 15 .

physDesc.accMat:
There is an AM-slip attached to the beginning of the volume which reads: Hrolfs karaka saga
med . hendi Sera Jons i Villinga Hollte
lied mier af Jonn Þorlakssyne 1709.
og sidann salld 1710.
var tilforna i innbundinni bok.
Þessa Hrolfs Sögu hefi eg läted con
ferera vid eitt mitt exemplar in 4to

origin.p: Written in Iceland in the seventeenth century.

acquisition.p: All we know for certain about the history of this MS is how Árni Magnússon acquired it. According to the AM-slip he borrowed it from Jón Þorláksson in 1709 and in 1710 he brought it from him. AM 9 fol was at that time bound at the very front of a larger codex. Árni Magnússon subsequently removed the saga from the volume and bound it seperately.
